r\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">What tools are commonly used for UX audits?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>To run UX audits, you\u2019ll want a mixture of tools that can help with analytics, session recordings, usability testing, and documentation. Examples of tools that are often used for these purposes include:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Google Analytics<\/li>\n<li>Hotjar<\/li>\n<li>Maze<\/li>\n<li>Lighthouse<\/li>\n<li>Notion<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                          <\/div>\n                  <\/dd>\n                              <\/div>\n                          <!-- Each FAQ item is a Question, linked via mainEntity -->\n              <div class=\"accordion-item open\" data-cursor=\"hover\" itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Question\">\n                                  <dt class=\"accordion-item-title\">\n                    <h4 class=\"long\" itemprop=\"name\">What are common mistakes when running a UX audit?<\/h4>\n                    <div class=\"icon\"><\/div>\n                  <\/dt>\n                \n                                  <dd class=\"accordion-item-content\">\n                    <div class=\"accordion-item-content-inner wysiwyg\">\n                      <!-- Accepted answer content -->\n                      <div itemprop=\"acceptedAnswer\" itemscope itemtype=\"https:\/\/schema.org\/Answer\">\n                        <div itemprop=\"text\">\n                          <p>The following are common mistakes business owners make when conducting UX audits:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Jumping straight into usability testing without first defining what they want to learn<\/li>\n<li>Failing to combine quantitative data with qualitative insights<\/li>\n<li>Completing only a visual design review and forgetting to check accessibility too<\/li>\n<li>Using their own employees for usability testing<\/li>\n<li>Forgetting to document and prioritise findings<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n                        <\/div>\n                      <\/div>\n\n                      <!-- Feedback UI is left as-is, not part of the schema answer -->\n                                              <div data-question-group>\n                          <div class=\"flex gap-4 mb-4\" data-question-ask>\n                            <strong>Did this answer your question?<\/strong>\n                            <span class=\"relative text-green cursor-pointer\" data-question=\"yes\">\n                              Yes\n                              <div class=\"faq-pop-up\" data-question-display=\"yes\">\n                                That\u2019s great glad we could help!\n                                <a href=\"\/contact-us\/\" target=\"_self\" class=\"btn btn-pink btn-small\" data-mp=\"\">\n                                  <span class=\"btn-bg\" data-mp-item=\"\" data-mp-scale=\"1.05\" data-mp-d=\"0.2\"><\/span>\n                                  <span class=\"btn-label\" data-mp-item=\"\">\n                                                                          Start a Project                                                                      <\/span>\n                                <\/a>\n                              <\/div>\n       